data.chText: 访问；拜访；看望；参观
data.enText: to go to see a person or a place for a period of time

data.chText: 她去威尔士看望亲戚了。
data.enText: She went to visit relatives in Wales.

data.chText: 首相目前正在访问日本。
data.enText: The Prime Minister is visiting Japan at the moment.

data.chText: 你应该每年至少去看两次牙科医生。
data.enText: You should visit your dentist at least twice a year.

data.chText: 访问（互联网上的网站）
data.enText: to go to a website on the Internet

data.chText: 欲知详情，请访问我们的网站。
data.enText: For more information, visit our website.

data.chText: （短暂地）作客，逗留
data.enText: to stay somewhere for a short time

data.chText: 我们不住在这里，只作短期停留。
data.enText: We don't live here. We're just visiting.

data.chText: 夏天也有海豹游到这湖里来。
data.enText: The lake is also visited by seals in the summer.

data.chText: 视察；巡视
data.enText: to make an official visit to sb, for example to perform checks or give advice

data.chText: 视察学校的政府检察员
data.enText: government inspectors visiting schools
visit sth on/upon sb/sth

data.chText: 对…进行惩罚
data.enText: to punish sb/sth

data.chText: 父辈作的孽报应到子女头上。
data.enText: The sins of the fathers are visited upon the children (= children are blamed or suffer for what their parents have done) .
visit with sb

data.chText: 与某人聊天；与某人闲谈
data.enText: to spend time with sb, especially talking socially

data.chText: 找个时间来跟我聊聊吧。
data.enText: Come and visit with me some time.

data.chText: 访问；参观；游览；逗留；看望
data.enText: an occasion or a period of time when sb goes to see a place or person and spends time there

data.chText: 这是我第一次访问纽约。
data.enText: It's my first visit to New York.

data.chText: 他们到法国进行互访。
data.enText: They're on an exchange visit to France.

data.chText: 你若有空，参观一下当地的博物馆。
data.enText: If you have time, pay a visit to the local museum.

data.chText: 昨晚警察来我们家了。
data.enText: We had a visit from the police last night.

data.chText: 这是社交性的拜访，还是业务性的？
data.enText: Is this a social visit , or is it business?

data.chText: 看医生
data.enText: a visit to the doctor

data.chText: 上门出诊
data.enText: a home visit (= when your doctor visits you)

data.chText: （到网站的）访问
data.enText: an occasion when sb looks at a website on the Internet

data.chText: 我们网站的访问人次一年内翻了一番。
data.enText: Visits to our website have doubled in a year.

data.chText: 碰头；会面
data.enText: an occasion when two or more people meet to talk in an informal way

ex.chText: 他多久去看望祖父母一次？
ex.enText: How often does he visit his grandparents?

ex.chText: 每个月有600多人访问他们的网站。
ex.enText: Over 600 people visit their website every month.

synonyms.bx: 指看望某人，也指浏览因特网的网站。

ex.chText: 我到城里之后会去看你。
ex.enText: I will call on you when I am in town.

ex.chText: 苏珊刚生了个儿子，我们去看看她吧。
ex.enText: Let's call on Susan. She just gave birth to a boy.

synonyms.bx: 指短暂地拜访或看望某人。

ex.chText: 她只是顺道来看看儿子过得怎么样。
ex.enText: She just dropped by to see how her son was getting on.

ex.chText: 她今天上午顺道来我办公室告诉我她要结婚了。
ex.enText: She dropped by my office this morning to tell me that she was getting married.

ex.chText: 你哪天过来喝杯咖啡怎么样？
ex.enText: Why not drop in for a coffee someday?

synonyms.bx: 指拜访相识的人，通常未事先约定好时间，常后接副词 by/in 或介词 into。

data.enText: visit sth on/upon sb/sth

data.chText: 对…进行惩罚
data.enText: to punish sb/sth

data.chText: 父辈作的孽报应到子女头上。
data.enText: The sins of the fathers are visited upon the children (= children are blamed or suffer for what their parents have done) .
visit with sb

data.chText: 与某人聊天；与某人闲谈
data.enText: to spend time with sb, especially talking socially

data.chText: 找个时间来跟我聊聊吧。
data.enText: Come and visit with me some time.

tr: a temporary stay (e.g., as a guest)
the act of going to see some person in a professional capacity
the act of visiting in an official capacity (as for an inspection)
the act of going to see some person or place or thing for a short time
example: he dropped by for a visit

tr: a meeting arranged by the visitor to see someone (such as a doctor or lawyer) for treatment or advice
example: he scheduled a visit to the dentist
He was visited with a terrible illness that killed him quickly
The principal visited his rage on the students

tr: talk socially without exchanging too much information
example: the men were sitting in the cafe and shooting the breeze

tr: go to certain places as for sightseeing
come to see in an official or professional capacity
example: The grant administrator visited the laboratory
The mayor likes to call on some of the prominent citizens

tr: go to see a place, as for entertainment
example: We went to see the Eiffel Tower in the morning
Every summer, we visited our relatives in the country for a month

value.def: If you visit someone, you go to see them and spend time with them.

example.ex: He wanted to visit his brother in Worcester...
example.tran: 他想去看望住在伍斯特的哥哥。

example.ex: He was visited by an old friend from Iraq...
example.tran: 一位来自伊拉克的老朋友来看望他。

example.ex: Helen had recently paid him a visit.

value.def: If you visit a place, you go there for a short time.

example.ex: He'll be visiting four cities including Cagliari in Sardinia...
example.tran: 他将要访问4个城市，包括萨迪尼亚的卡利亚里。

example.ex: Caroline visited all the big stores.
example.tran: 卡罗琳光顾了所有的大型商店。

example.ex: I paid a visit to my local print shop.
example.tran: 我去了我们当地的照片冲洗店。

value.def: If you visit a website, you look at it.

example.ex: For details visit our website at www.cobuild.collins.co.uk.
example.tran: 欲知详情，请访问我们的网站www.cobuild.collins.co.uk。

value.def: If you visit a professional person such as a doctor or lawyer, you go and see them in order to get professional advice. If they visit you, they come to see you in order to give you professional advice.

example.ex: If necessary the patient can then visit his doctor for further advice...
example.tran: 如有必要，病人可以上门咨询自己的医生以得到更多的建议。

example.ex: A doctor will visit you in your apartment.
example.tran: 会有医生到您的住所出诊。

example.ex: You may have regular home visits from a neonatal nurse.
example.tran: 可以雇请育婴护士定期到家里提供服务。

value.tran: 上门咨询（专业人士）;（专业人士）上门服务

value.def: If something very unpleasant is visited upon you, it happens to you.

example.ex: Violence is visited upon us every day...
example.tran: 暴力事件每天都会降临在我们身上。

example.ex: Death and suffering had been visited on thousands of innocents.
example.tran: 死亡和苦难降临在了数千名无辜的人身上。
